Description: Name of the server as it appears in the client server browser.
Long form description of the server when clicked on in the client server browser.
If enabled, the server will appear in the client server browser.
Password required to connect to the server (except for whitelisted players). Default is no password.
Category of the server shown when clients first select a new game.
Maximum number of connections allowed at one time. -1 = infinite.
Internal server IP address that the server should bind to. Default is Any (all IPs on the host).
Internal server IP address tha the RCON server should bind to. Default is Any (all IPs on the host).

Maximum active players, 0 = Unrestricted. Setting this gives your match score a boost in the server browser when you have fewer players than needed, and an extra boost if players have recently abandoned. Affects your server score only and not the total users that can connect.
The address of a Discord server used for players on the server.
When enabled, UPnP will be enabled on the server. Requires a UPnP-enabled router to work.
Name of the save to load at startup.
How often to write changed data to disk.
When enabled, removes failed to load objects upon loading.
Path for storage (leave as "Storage" for default settings).
Path to file to start game from for a new world, if blank (null) then the world will be generated.
Defines the announcement countdown intervalss. The second countdown is handled by the Countdown Start setting. -1 = disabled)
Specifies the message to be sent when the automatic restart auto shutdown occurs.
Specifies how many seconds until the shutdown counter starts.

Web server URL. If not specified then remote IP address will be used. Usually should be ignored, but may be desired to use SSL or a friendly name. Uses default http/https port if not explicit port specified. Format: http(s)://myserver.com:[port]

The user account associated with the server. This will be shared with clients and will allow achievements earned by players on this server to be visible in other servers (as well as future features to come). Visit [play.eco](https://play.eco/) to link your steam account or create a new account.
Password for the SLG Account.
When enabled, allows beta branches (branches other than "public") to be installed. Specify the branch under "Selected Beta Branch". NOTE: Update the server after switching branches!

[Beta branch](https://steamdb.info/app/739590/depots/) to install. Requires "Enable Beta Branch" to be enabled. Set any required password under "Beta Password". NOTE: Update the server after switching branches!
Scales how much time of day matches real time. Higher numbers result in shorter day/night cycles (as a value of X seconds per real-world second), but will not affect simulation speed.
Game progress time advances at this rate.
Multiplier applied to the cost of learning a specialty. Values below 1 decrease specialty cost, above 1 increase specialty cost.
The default experience gain for all players, regardless of their other sources of experience points and difficulty settings.
Multiplier applied to the rate of skill points gained over time. Values below 1 decrease the rate, above 1 increase the rate.
Scales skill penalty to suffocation. 0 to disable.
Factors into experience per level specialties. Default is 25, higher values increase experience requirement, lower values reduce it.
Multiplier applied to crafting resource cost. Values below 1 decrease crafting resource cost, above 1 increase resource cost.
Multiplier applied to crafting time. Values below 1 decrease crafting time, above 1 increase crafting time.
Percentage to refund a player when they remove a specialty.
Percentage of specialty experience that is also gained as level experience. Not recommended for public servers. Default is 0.0
Multiplier applied to item maximum stack size. Values below 1 decrease maximum size, above 1 increases maximum size. A server restart is required for correct calculation.
Multiplier applied to item weight. Values below 1 decrease item weight, above 1 increase item weight. A server restart is required for correct calculation.
Multiplier applied to fuel yield per unit. Values below 1 decrease yield, above 1 increase yield. A server restart is required for correct calculation.
Global scale for how quickly plants mature.
Multiplier applied to storage connection range. Values below 1 decrease range, above 1 increases range. A server restart is required for correct calculation.
Endgame crafting cost presets for Laser and Computer Lab. Does not affect work orders in progress.
Adjusts the default shelf life of all foods, with higher values causing food to last longer. For example, setting to 2 doubles the shelf life while setting to 0.5 halves the shelf life.
Maximum hours a user can play per day. After their allotted time, they can still play but not expand calories with work. 0 means no limit.
When enabled, remaining playtime can be added to the next day.
If Rollover Daily Playtime is enabled, this sets the maximum hours playtime in a day. This limits how much playtime a player can save up by not playing.
When enabled, a meteor will exist in the world.
Time in days when the meteor will impact. Changing this value will override impact time for the current active meteor.
When enabled, allows players to rent access to a given deed from another.
When enabled, players will be able to use voice chat.
When enabled, the variety of food a player eats will provide a bonus.
When enabled, each player has unique preferences for each type of food that yields a bonus, and periodic "cravings" will emerge for an additional bonus.
When enabled, the world will be on pause.
When enabled, the world will resume as soon as the first player logs in.
When enabled, rooms can have empty blocks serve as windows and still count as rooms.
Repeated rooms earn this multiple value of the previous ones. This makes duplicate rooms less valuable in a house.
Specifies how many wall blocks are required to make one empty window or door block without penalty. It counts all wall blocks in the room, including window blocks.
When enabled, time will accelerate if all online players sleep in a bed. This shouldn't be enabled for public servers!
The maximum time multiplier that will pass while sleeping. Lower this to make the simulation fast-forward more reliably.

DisplayName: Time To Reach Maximum Time Rate
Description: How long it takes to reach the maximum sleep time. Makes for a smooth transition into sleeping.

When enabled, overthrowing a government will be allowed and a constitution with higher house value than the current can be ratified. It will also be impossible to make laws about placing or crafting a constitution.
To overthrow an existing government, a constitution must be placed in a building that exceeds the previous constitution's value by this percentage. 100 = 100%.
The "Active Players" demographic will check this many of the past days to determine the hours played by a user.

DisplayName: Hours Played To Be Active Demographic
Description: The "Active Players" demographic will apply to any users who played this many hours within the specified Day Range.

DisplayName: Long Term Demographic Active Days Percentage
Description: Percentage of days a user needs to be considered active (as determined by the Hours Played To Be Active setting) to be in the "Long Term" demographic. 1 = 100%.
The "Abandoned Players" demographic will check this many past days for hours played by the user.

DisplayName: Hours Played To Be Abandoned Demographic
Description: The "Abandoned Players" demographic will apply to any users who have not played more than this many hours within the past number of days specified in the Day Range setting.
The "Abandoned Players" demographic will only apply to users who have a citizen age greater than this many hours.
Demographics are updated after this much time has passed.

DisplayName: Allow Invalid Civic Container Time In Minutes
Description: Sets how much time can a civics object have an invalid or missing host object before it goes invalid
Recurring transfers like rent and wages are paid after this many minutes.

DisplayName: Allow Laws To Prevent Login Or Play
Description: When enabled, laws can prevent someone from logging in or playing. Enable with caution: users can create a law that blocks everyone from logging.
After this many hours, an election will end with or without a winner.
An election will not produce a winner unless this percentage of eligible voters have cast their vote.
Once an election of a certain type completes, another of the same type cannot be started for this many days.

DisplayName: End Election Early When This Percent Have Voted
Description: If this percentage of voters have cast their vote, then the election will end early (but not sooner than the Minimum Election Time).

DisplayName: Percent Of All Voters To Instant Win
Description: If this percent of all possible voters votes yes, the election will finish instantly.

DisplayName: Percent Of All Voters To Instant Lose
Description: If this percent of all possible voters votes no, the election will fail instantly.
When enabled, the way a citizen votes will be hidden
The percentage value a vote from a Twitch viewer counts relative to vote from a player.
The maximum percentage contribution all combined Twitch voters can have in an election.
The currently selected language. If you change languages, you'll need to restart the server for the changes to fully take effect.
Determines how much of any CPU core can be used by the server. Defaults to 25%, and should supposedly not be set higher than 75%.
An experimental feature that allows parallel (as opposed to sequential) world object ticks. May increase performance at the cost of stability.
Minimum distance between trees. Lower values can impact performance negatively.

Maximum number of tooltip parts stored in server's cache. Lowering this number can reduce RAM usage, but may impact response time for user's tooltip request. Changing this setting will take effect after server restart.
Rate at which the server updates to clients, per second.
